Document: VisibleOnScreenEnabler3D  
Path: godot/classes/class_visibleonscreenenabler3d.rst  
Summary: Properties for configuring node activation based on screen visibility and target node path.  

enable_mode (EnableMode): Determines how the target node is enabled. Corresponds to Node.PROCESS_MODE_DISABLED when the node is disabled. Set via set_enable_mode(value: EnableMode), retrieved via get_enable_mode() → EnableMode. Note: When disabled, the node always uses Node.PROCESS_MODE_DISABLED.  

enable_node_path (NodePath): The path to the target node, relative to VisibleOnScreenEnabler3D. Set via set_enable_node_path(value: NodePath), retrieved via get_enable_node_path() → NodePath. Note: The target node is cached when the VisibleOnScreenEnabler3D enters the scene tree. If the path is empty or invalid, an error is generated.